    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a family of around 10,000 species of insects that are social, live in colonies often having three castes, have a large head, a slender, oval abdomen joined to the thorax by a small waist, one one or two finlike extensions running across the thin waist region, and elbowed antennae.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
